item.title: 西南航空公司下调第一季度单位收入增长预期
item.description: 由于担心关税压力和政府支出的不确定性会影响国内旅游需求，西南航空公司周二下调了单位收入增长预期。【原文：Southwest Airlines cut its unit revenue growth forecast on Tuesday, as concerns over discretionary spending amid tariff pressures and government spending uncertainties affect domestic travel demand.】

item.title: 美国 华尔街史诗般的暴跌抹去了特朗普的涨幅
item.description: 美国早报【原文：Morning Bid U.S.】

item.title: 西南航空转向付费行李政策以提高收益
item.description: 美国西南航空公司（Southwest Airlines）周二表示，该公司将开始向部分乘客收取托运行李费用，结束独特的免费政策，同时该公司也在寻找支撑其盈利的方法。【原文：Southwest Airlines said on Tuesday it would start charging some customers for checked bags, ending a unique free policy, as the company looks for ways to shore up its earnings.】

item.title: 西南航空转向付费行李政策以提高收益
item.description: 美国西南航空公司（Southwest Airlines）周二表示，该公司将开始向部分乘客收取托运行李费用，结束独特的免费政策，同时该公司正在寻找支撑其盈利的方法。【原文：Southwest Airlines said on Tuesday it would start charging some customers for checked bags, ending a unique free policy, as the company looks for ways to shore up its earnings.】

item.title: 宝莹所有者汉高称美国政策损害了北美市场
item.description: 消费品和粘合剂生产商汉高周二表示，美国政府的决定对北美市场造成了极大的伤害，这是最新一家就唐纳德-特朗普总统的贸易政策所带来的不确定性发出警告的公司。【原文：U.S. government decisions are hurting the North American market disproportionately, consumer goods and adhesive maker Henkel said on Tuesday, the latest company to warn about uncertainty caused by President Donald Trump's trade policies.】

item.title: 华尔街大跌后期货走高，就业数据值得期待
item.description: 继华尔街主要股指在上一交易日创下今年最大单日跌幅之后，周二美国股指期货在当天晚些时候的就业数据公布前小幅上扬。【原文：U.S. stock index futures inched up on Tuesday following this year's biggest one-day drop for Wall Street's main indexes in the previous session, ahead of jobs data later in the day.】

item.title: 美国汽车买家争相前往经销商处，以避免与关税相关的价格上涨
item.description: 马修-米切尔（Matthew Mitchell）听说美国总统唐纳德-特朗普真的要对墨西哥和加拿大征收 25% 的关税后，他告诉妻子是时候抢购一辆汽车了，而且要快。【原文：After Matthew Mitchell heard U.S. President Donald Trump was serious about implementing 25% tariffs on Mexico and Canada, he told his wife it was time to snatch up a car, and fast.】

item.title: 特朗普会见美国企业界人士，经济担忧打压股市
item.description: 预计总统将与约 100 位首席执行官发表讲话。【原文：The president is expected to speak with around 100 CEOs.】

item.title: 独家报道：Meta 开始测试其首个内部人工智能训练芯片
item.description: 两位消息人士告诉路透社，Facebook 的所有者 Meta 正在测试其第一款用于训练人工智能系统的内部芯片，这是该公司迈向设计更多自己的定制芯片、减少对 Nvidia 等外部供应商依赖的一个重要里程碑。【原文：Facebook owner Meta is testing its first in-house chip for training artificial intelligence systems, a key milestone as it moves to design more of its own custom silicon and reduce reliance on external suppliers like Nvidia , two sources told Reuters.】

item.title: 特朗普焦虑情绪加深，美国散户投资者警惕买入跌势
item.description: 对特朗普关税将引发经济衰退的担忧正在推动股市抛售。【原文：Fears that Trump’s tariffs will spark an economic downturn are driving a sell-off in equities.】

item.title: 特朗普的关税给威斯康星州的工厂车间带来了 "狂野的西部"。
item.description: 阿里恩斯公司（AriensCo）是一家生产鲜艳橙色吹雪机的公司，自 11 月份以来，该公司一直在为关税寒流做准备。【原文：AriensCo - a manufacturer of bright orange snowblowers - has braced for the cold blast of tariffs since November.】

item.title: 2 月份美国小型企业信心指数跌幅扩大
item.description: 由于对美国政府贸易政策的担忧与日俱增，2 月份美国小企业信心连续第三个月下降，抹去了唐纳德-特朗普总统 11 月赢得大选后取得的大部分涨幅。【原文：U.S. small-business confidence dropped for a third straight month in February, wiping away much of the gains notched in the aftermath of President Donald Trump's election victory in November, amid mounting concerns over the administration's trade policy.】

item.title: Coinbase 在印度金融监管部门注册，提供加密货币交易服务
item.description: 总部位于美国的加密货币交易所 Coinbase Global 周二表示，该公司已在印度金融情报机构（FIU）注册，允许在印度提供加密货币交易服务。【原文：U.S.-headquartered cryptocurrency exchange Coinbase Global has registered with India's Financial Intelligence Unit (FIU), allowing it to offer crypto trading services in the country, the company said on Tuesday.】

item.title: 达美航空下调预期令投资者恐慌，美国航空股暴跌
item.description: 达美航空公司（Delta Air Lines）下调了利润预期，激起了人们对美国经济疲软对旅行造成的冲击的担忧，美国主要航空公司的股票在周二的盘前交易中大幅下跌。【原文：Shares of major U.S. airlines slumped in premarket trading on Tuesday after Delta Air Lines slashed its profit forecast, stoking concerns about the hit to travel from a weakening U.S. economy.】

item.title: 波兰在与美国的最新争执中对大型科技征税计划采取强硬态度
item.description: 波兰副总理周二誓言坚持对大型科技公司征收新税的计划，回击了即将上任的美国大使的报复威胁，华沙与华盛顿之间的口水战正在加深。【原文：Poland's deputy prime minister vowed on Tuesday to stick with plans to introduce a new tax on big tech, hitting back at a threat of retaliation from the incoming United States ambassador amid a deepening war of words between Warsaw and Washington.】

item.title: 雷诺表示埃斯皮诺萨对继续保持雷诺/日产关系充满信心
item.description: 法国汽车制造商雷诺周二表示，注意到日产汽车宣布其首席规划官伊万-埃斯皮诺萨（Ivan Espinosa）将从 4 月 1 日起接替内田诚（Makoto Uchida）成为这家陷入困境的日本汽车制造商的领导者。【原文：French carmaker Renault said on Tuesday it was taking note of Nissan's announcement that Ivan Espinosa, its chief planning officer, would take the helm from April 1, succeeding Makoto Uchida as leader of the troubled Japanese carmaker.】

item.title: 据 El Confidencial 报道，法航荷航出价 3 亿欧元收购欧罗巴航空公司 51%的股份
item.description: 新闻网站 El Confidencial 周二援引接近谈判的未具名消息人士的话称，法荷航空集团法航-荷航（Air France-KLM）已出价 3 亿欧元（约合 3.2682 亿美元）收购西班牙欧罗巴航空公司（Air Europa）51% 的股份。【原文：Franco-Dutch airlines group Air France-KLM has offered 300 million euros ($326.82 million) for a 51% stake in Spanish airline Air Europa, news website El Confidencial said on Tuesday, citing unnamed sources close to the negotiations.】

item.title: 大韩航空斥资 13 亿美元收购韩亚航空后推出新品牌
item.description: 大韩航空（Korean Air）周二推出了新的飞机涂装和企业品牌，该公司将与韩国竞争对手韩亚航空（Asiana Airlines）合并，成为亚洲最大的航空公司之一。【原文：Korean Air on Tuesday launched new aircraft livery and corporate branding that will be introduced across the airline as it combines with South Korean rival Asiana Airlines to become one of Asia's biggest carriers.】

item.title: 西班牙时装零售商 Mango 首席执行官表示正在适应美国关税政策
item.description: 西班牙时装零售商 Mango 首席执行官表示，该公司正在适应特朗普政府对从中国进口商品征收的关税，并可能重新考虑在美国这个第五大市场销售的产品类型。【原文：Spanish fashion retailer Mango is adapting to tariffs imposed by the Trump administration on imports from China and could rethink the types of products it sells in the U.S., which is its fifth-largest market, the company's chief executive said.】

item.title: 印度将近 300 名从东南亚诈骗中心获救的公民带回家
item.description: 印度政府表示，印度已将近 300 名国民遣送回国，他们被诱骗到包括缅甸在内的多个东南亚国家，以虚假工作机会为诱饵，在诈骗团伙中从事网络犯罪和其他欺诈活动。【原文：India has brought home nearly 300 of its nationals who were lured to various southeast Asian countries, including Myanmar, with fake job offers and made to engage in cybercrime and other fraudulent activities in scam compounds, the government said.】

item.title: 乐高销售额上升，更多购物者喜欢乐高积木
item.description: 乐高公司报告称，随着越来越多的购物者抢购其彩色塑料砖建筑套件，2024 年的销售额增长强劲，该玩具制造商称，它正在从竞争对手手中抢夺市场份额。【原文：Lego reported strong sales growth for 2024 as more shoppers snapped up its colourful plastic brick construction sets and the toymaker said it was taking market share from rivals.】

item.title: 部长表示，VinFast 计划在印尼全国安装电动汽车充电站
item.description: 印尼总统普拉博沃-苏比安托（Prabowo Subianto）周二会见了越南电动汽车制造商VinFast的代表，印尼投资部长表示，越南电动汽车制造商VinFast计划在全国安装多达10万个充电站。【原文：Indonesia's investment minister said that Vietnamese electric vehicle maker VinFast planned to install as many as 100,000 charging stations across the country, after President Prabowo Subianto met company representatives on Tuesday.】

item.title: 中国零售交易商拥抱 DeepSeek，向学者致敬
item.description: 如果你无法对抗他们，那就加入他们吧，这是中国母婴投资者的口头禅，他们正在拥抱 DeepSeek 和其他人工智能工具，这与去年政府打击计算机驱动的量化交易员形成了鲜明对比。【原文：If you cannot fight them, join them, is the mantra among Chinese mom-and-pop investors who are embracing DeepSeek and other artificial intelligence tools, in sharp contrast with last year's government crackdown on computer-driven quantitative traders.】

item.title: 如果欧洲建造千兆工厂，人工智能产业会出现吗？
item.description: 作为欧洲在人工智能领域追赶美国和中国战略的一部分，欧盟委员会正在筹集200亿美元建设四个 "人工智能千兆工厂"，但一些行业专家质疑建设这些工厂是否合理。【原文：The European Commission is raising $20 billion to construct four "AI gigafactories" as part of Europe's strategy to catch up with the U.S. and China on artificial intelligence, but some industry experts question whether it makes sense to build them.】

item.title: 瑞士上议院支持限制银行家薪酬的动议
item.description: 瑞士议会上院周一晚些时候以微弱优势支持一项动议，将银行家的年薪总额限制在 300 万至 500 万瑞士法郎（约合 340 万至 570 万美元）之间，这一数额大大低于目前最高薪银行家的收入。【原文：The Swiss upper house of parliament late on Monday narrowly backed a motion to limit bankers' total annual compensation to between 3 and 5 million Swiss francs ($3.4-5.7 million), a sum significantly below what the best-paid earn today.】

item.title: 英国多米诺比萨公布年度核心利润增长
item.description: 英国多米诺比萨集团周二公布的年度基本核心利润增长了约 4%，原因是折扣产品促进了订单的增加。【原文：Britain's Domino's Pizza Group reported an about 4% rise in underlying annual core profit on Tuesday, on increasing orders boosted by discount offerings.】

item.title: 汉高预计2025年销售额将继续增长
item.description: 德国消费品和粘合剂生产商汉高公司周二预测，2025年的有机销售额增长率将达到3.5%，理由是公司正在实施其增长议程，而此前该公司2024年的增长未能达到市场预期。【原文：Henkel forecast organic sales growth of up to 3.5% for 2025 on Tuesday, citing the implementation of its growth agenda, after the German consumer goods and adhesives maker's 2024 growth missed market expectations.】

item.title: 在贸易紧张局势和新竞争对手的冲击下，大众汽车对 2025 年的前景保持缄默
item.description: 大众汽车周二表示，预计 2025 年的营业利润率将从 2024 年的 5.9% 降至 5.5-6.5%，与其他竞争对手一样，对未来一年的前景作出了低调的展望，因为汽车行业正在与需求疲软、成本高企和一触即发的贸易紧张局势作斗争。【原文：Volkswagen on Tuesday said it expects an operating margin of 5.5-6.5% in 2025, from 5.9% in 2024, joining rivals in giving a muted outlook for the year ahead as the sector battles weak demand, high costs and simmering trade tensions.】

item.title: 阿布扎比 ADQ 公司获得物流公司 Aramex 的多数股权
item.description: 阿布扎比主权财富基金 ADQ 周二表示，在完成要约收购后，该基金目前持有物流公司 Aramex 58% 的股份。【原文：Abu Dhabi sovereign wealth fund ADQ on Tuesday said it now owns a 58% stake in logistics firm Aramex after completing a tender offer.】

item.title: 特朗普称将购买 "新特斯拉 "以示对马斯克的支持
item.description: 美国总统唐纳德-特朗普（Donald Trump）周二表示，他将购买一辆新的特斯拉汽车，以示对这家电动汽车制造商的掌门人及其盟友埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）的支持。【原文：U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday said he will buy a new Tesla car to show support for the electric carmaker's chief and his ally Elon Musk amid recent "Tesla Takedown" protests and the slump in the company's stock price.】
